:: END Safehouse is Safe {"position":"1000,1300","size":"100,100"}
<<type 60ms>>
Other then the rare scavenger, no one approaches the safehouse. 

After a few weeks, a sense of security begins to form, and your paranoia and feeling of uneasiness start to fade away. 

You decide to stay. It's not a luxurious life, but it has everything you need to survive and thrive and decide that you'll hang out inside until it the situation resolves itself, or until you die, whichever comes first.

END
<</type>>


:: END Safety is Assured {"position":"1325,1575","size":"100,100"}
<<type 60ms>>
The next morning, you decide to head out and discover a map in the glove box, along with some documents. 

The map points toward the state border, outside of the Exclusion Zone. 

You follow it.

Somehow, the trail is clear of any dangers.

As you cross the border, scientists and government agents notice your presence and transport you back to civilization. 

The nightmare is over. 

END
<</type>>


